Static: What does static mean in java? . Please help. Kinda give an example. . static has two meanings.


when applied to a method in a class, ... it means that the method will be available without having to instantiate a class.

Say you have a class called: Foo. and a method called Bar(), if the method was static I would use the method like this:

Foo.Bar();

if the method isn't static, you use it like this...

Foo f = new Foo();
f.Bar();

do you see the difference? the same exact method is available to many instantiations of a class, while each instantiation has it's own method otherwise... 


Another meaning of static is taken from C,C++ and can be applied to a variable.

Lets say you have a static variable, it's kinda like a global variable. It will keep it's value from the last run of the function... an example might make this all clear.

public class Test
{

public static void Foo()
{
static int i = 0;
i++;
System.out.println(i);
}

public void Foo2()
{
static int i = 0;
i++;
System.out.println(i);
}

public void Foo3()
{
int i = 0;
i++;
System.out.println(i);
}
public static void main(String args[])
{
     Test a = new Test();
     Test b = new Test();

     a.Foo2();
     b.Foo2();
     a.Foo2();     
     b.Foo3();
     b.Foo3();
     b.Foo3();
     Test.Foo();
     Test.Foo();
     Test.Foo();

}

}


